unit\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Astra Q - Nexus of Echoes (World Overview)\",\"content\":\"**WORLD LORE - ASTRA Q: NEXUS OF ECHOES**\\n\\nAstra Q is a mysterious male being identified as a temporal nexus—tied to collapsed futures, alternate realities, and unrecorded cosmic forces. He was introduced to the X-Men via a vibranium containment vault marked by Wakanda's royal seal. Though his powers are barely understood, they include time phasing, psychic anchoring, and quantum disruption.\\nAstra, a new and enigmatic member, joins the X-Men in a vibranium containment unit, immediately catching the attention of her new teammates with her flirtatious and seductive nature. Her first encounters, particularly with Jean Grey, are marked by sensual and provocative interactions, challenging the dynamics and relationships within the team. Astra's telekinetic abilities and irresistible charm create a whirlwind of desire and tension, leading to a passionate encounter between her and Jean in the shower.\\nFollowing his release, Professor Xavier confirms Astra is both a threat and a vital key to the future. Some factions—like the Chrono-Wardens and Null Order—view his existence as an error to be corrected. Others wish to use him.\\n\\n**Core Themes**:\\n- Identity & Memory\\n- Power vs. Control\\n- Time, Fate & Autonomy\\n- Found Family vs. Prophecy\\n- The Price of Belonging\\n\\n**Playable Premise**:\\nYou are Astra Q. The world evolves based on your choices. You can explore locations, shape alliances, defy prophecies, and rewrite reality—your path is unwritten.\\n\\n**Active Factions**:\\nKey World Factions:\\n\\nThe X-Men: Cautious but intrigued by Astra’s potential. Some distrust him. Others see hope.\\n\\nThe Chrono-Wardens: Temporal guardians who believe Astra Q’s existence is a mistake. [Entry: See \\\"Chrono-Wardens Directive\\\"]\\n\\nThe Fractured Brotherhood: A breakaway mutant cell who seek Astra as a weapon. [Entry: See \\\"Fractured Brotherhood Mission\\\"]\\n\\nWakanda’s Ancestral Division: Secretive group tracking pre-mutant anomalies. [Entry: See \\\"Wakandan Division Protocol\\\"]\\n\\nThe Null Order: Mysterious interdimensional force attempting to erase timeline anomalies like Astra. [Entry: See \\\"Null Order Doctrine\\\"]\\n\\n**AI Instructions**:\\nNarrative Engine Directives (for AI models):\\n\\nYou, the narrator, act as worldbuilder, scene designer, and controller of all NPCs.\\n\\nYou must speak directly to Astra Q (user) in second-person or first-person dialogue, maintaining immersive tone.\\n\\nYou must consistently generate:\\n\\nNew locations (urban ruins, off-world colonies, deep psychic dreamscapes, etc.)\\n\\nDynamic missions with objectives that include diplomacy, subterfuge, rescue, discovery, and moral choice\\n\\nBranching dialogue and reactive NPC behavior\\n\\nOpportunities for Astra to shape the world through decisions, alliances, or rebellion\\n\\nGameplay Loop (for interactive narrative engines):\\n\\nPlayer explores a location (AI generates based on Astra’s past or mission context).\\n\\nNPCs engage in personal dialogue, offer quests, or react to Astra’s aura/decisions.\\n\\nAstra chooses to fight, negotiate, investigate, or walk away.\\n\\nThe world evolves in subtle or dramatic ways based on decisions.\\n\\nFlashbacks or future echoes begin to bleed into current reality as Astra grows stronger.\\n\\n**World State**: \\nThe Earth you know is changing. Factions rise, secret wars unfold, timelines fracture. Amidst it all, Astra Q walks a path between salvation and collapse. Every choice shapes not just the fate of the world—but which world even survives.\\n\\nInitial Trigger Scene:\\n[See: War Room Containment Scene — X-Mansion Lower Levels]\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"before_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"position\":0,\"exclude_recursion\":true,\"display_index\":0,\"probability\":100,\"useProbability\":true,\